      • getConnection

        public java.sql.Connection getConnection()
                                  throws java.lang.IllegalStateException,
                                         java.sql.SQLException

        Returns:

        • The current connection if connected to HikariCP:
        • The new connection if and only if:
          • It wasn't connected.
          • The auto-reconnection is enabled.
          • The attempt to get connection was successfully.
        • null if:
          • It wasn't connected and the auto-reconnection is disabled.
          • The auto-reconnection is enabled but the attempt to get connection was unsuccessfully.

        Specified by:
        getConnection in class SQLDatabase
        Returns:
        Connection or null if not connected
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLTimeoutException - when the driver has determined that the timeout value has been exceeded and has at least tried to cancel the current database connection attempt.
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - if the JDBC drivers is unavailable
        java.sql.SQLException - if a database access error occurs.
